## Penalties for late payment and late submission

The way that HMRC penalises late payments and late submissions is changing. For customers using Making Tax Digital for Income Tax, new penalties will replace the current late submission and late payment penalties that apply to personal tax returns. 

You can find information about the rules and thresholds that relate to late submission and payment penalties on [GOV.UK](https://www.gov.uk/guidance/penalties-for-making-tax-digital-for-income-tax).

### Retrieving penalty details

To retrieve a customer’s penalty details, software should use the [Retrieve ITSA Penalties](https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk/api-documentation/docs/api/service/self-assessment-accounts-api/4.0/oas/page#tag/ITSA-Penalties/paths/~1accounts~1self-assessment~1%7Bnino%7D~1penalties/get) endpoint in the Self Assessment Accounts API, 24 months worth of penalty information will be returned.

