## Making a payment and claiming a refund

For an MTD Customer to make a payment they can still access the Self Assessment service via the [Pay your Self Assessment tax bill - Overview page on GOV.UK](https://www.gov.uk/pay-self-assessment-tax-bill).

To claim a refund, customers or their agents must access their HMRC online service and use the 'Request a Self Assessment Refund' service. Software can provide the following link for users to access these services - [HMRC online services: sign in or set up an account: Sign in or set up an account - GOV.UK](https://www.gov.uk/log-in-register-hmrc-online-services). Users will need to sign in with the User ID and Password they received when signing up for Making Tax Digital for Income Tax. 

When a refund has been requested, software will be able to show the amount the users have requested using the [Retrieve Self Assessment Balance and Transactions endpoint](https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk/api-documentation/docs/api/service/self-assessment-accounts-api/4.0/oas/page#tag/Payments-and-Liabilities/paths/~1accounts~1self-assessment~1%7Bnino%7D~1balance-and-transactions/get) and the `firstPendingAmountRequested` data item.

